{"nodes": [{"id": "models_cortex_md", "label": "cortex.md \u2014 Sparse-Cortex-LM Architecture Specification", "file_type": "document", "source_file": "models/cortex.md", "source_location": null, "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null}, {"id": "concept_cortex", "label": "Cortex / Sparse-Cortex (ternary + GDN + SWA hybrid architecture)", "file_type": "concept", "source_file": "models/cortex.md", "source_location": null, "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "Brain-inspired architecture combining BitNet b1.58 ternary weights, a hybrid GDN+SWA token mixer (~3 GDN layers per 1 SWA layer), ReLU^2 FFN sparsity, and (phase 3+) Mixture-of-Recursions adaptive depth. Embeddings, RMSNorm, and LM head are deliberately kept bf16 and never ternarized. Built as a staged plan \u2014 one lever at a time, each measured against the GPT-2 baseline before adding the next."}, {"id": "concept_bitlinear", "label": "BitLinear (native ternary weight linear layer)", "file_type": "concept", "source_file": "models/cortex.md", "source_location": null, "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "Drop-in replacement for nn.Linear: weights quantized to {-1,0,+1} via absmean (gamma=mean(|W|)), activations quantized to int8 via absmax per token, matmul becomes pure add/subtract. Backward uses a Straight-Through Estimator over a full-precision latent 'ghost' weight. Golden rules: never ternarize embeddings/RMSNorm/LM head (keep bf16); activations must be int8 never ternary (else the model collapses); train natively ternary from initialization, never post-training quantization (PTQ); no biases in BitLinear layers or norms; use ~2x the bf16 learning rate with a two-phase weight-decay schedule."}, {"id": "concept_gated_deltanet", "label": "Gated DeltaNet (GDN)", "file_type": "concept", "source_file": "models/cortex.md", "source_location": null, "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "Linear attention with delta-rule updates and gating; fixed-size recurrent state gives bounded VRAM and linear cost in sequence length. Gating enables fast erasure, the delta rule enables targeted updates. Its fixed-size state cannot store everything, which is exactly why it is paired with Sliding Window Attention layers \u2014 do not remove SWA thinking it's redundant, you would lose local recall."}, {"id": "concept_sliding_window_attention", "label": "Sliding Window Attention (SWA)", "file_type": "concept", "source_file": "models/cortex.md", "source_location": null, "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "Exact softmax attention restricted to a local window (e.g. 512 tokens). Recovers the precise local recall that GDN's compressed fixed-size state loses. Removing SWA layers loses recall \u2014 treated as a hard rule (checklist item, cortex.md sec 13)."}, {"id": "concept_relu2", "label": "Squared ReLU (ReLU^2) activation", "file_type": "concept", "source_file": "models/cortex.md", "source_location": null, "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "f(z) = max(0,z)^2. Induces ~90-95% emergent activation sparsity per-token (the 'lazy neuron phenomenon') without a predictor or extra machinery. At inference only the W_down columns for non-zero neurons need be computed. Optional L1 regularization on hidden activations can be added during training to push sparsity further. Alternative: dReLU / TurboSparse-style double ReLU."}, {"id": "concept_mixture_of_recursions", "label": "Mixture-of-Recursions (MoR)", "file_type": "concept", "source_file": "models/cortex.md", "source_location": null, "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "Phase-3+ adaptive-depth mechanism: a single weight-tied block is re-looped up to R times per token (e.g. R=3), with a router assigning recursion depth per token by learned difficulty (not post-hoc chain-of-thought). Double benefit: weight-tying reduces parameter count/VRAM, routing reduces FLOPs by only re-looping hard tokens. Requires a mandatory router homeostasis auxiliary loss (sigmoid depth probabilities + regularization) to prevent depth collapse (router always picking min or max depth). Supports per-recursion KV caching for still-active tokens only."}, {"id": "concept_mixture_of_depths", "label": "Mixture-of-Depths (MoD)", "file_type": "concept", "source_file": "models/cortex.md", "source_location": null, "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "Simpler precursor to MoR for phase 2 if MoR proves too complex up front: a per-block router lets only top-k tokens through the block, the rest skip via the residual. Fixed capacity gives a static compute graph, easier to implement than MoR."}, {"id": "concept_mixture_of_experts", "label": "Mixture-of-Experts (MoE)", "file_type": "concept", "source_file": "models/cortex.md", "source_location": null, "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "Late-phase, scale-only lever: replaces the FFN with N experts, top-k activated per token (e.g. N=8, k=2). Does NOT reduce VRAM \u2014 all experts must reside in memory to be routable \u2014 and underperforms at small scale; its compute gain only pays off once the model is large (~40B target). Requires mandatory load-balancing auxiliary loss (coeff ~0.01) or a few experts monopolize traffic while others atrophy."}, {"id": "concept_straight_through_estimator", "label": "Straight-Through Estimator (STE)", "file_type": "concept", "source_file": "models/cortex.md", "source_location": null, "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "Backward pass treats the forward quantization (BitLinear's ternary rounding) as identity: dL/dW ~= dL/dW_q, so gradients flow to a continuous full-precision latent weight even though the forward transmission is discrete."}, {"id": "concept_muon_optimizer", "label": "Muon optimizer", "file_type": "concept", "source_file": "models/cortex.md", "source_location": null, "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null}, {"id": "rationale_gdn_h1_pattern", "label": "GDN-H1 interleaving pattern (3 GDN : 1 SWA)", "file_type": "rationale", "source_file": "models/cortex.md", "source_location": null, "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "Recommended layer arrangement: interleave roughly 3 GDN layers per 1 SWA layer (9 GDN + 3 SWA across 12 layers in the Phase-1 124M config). GDN compresses long history, SWA guarantees exact local recall \u2014 considered the best current compromise for small models."}, {"id": "rationale_vram_vs_compute_principle", "label": "VRAM vs Compute independence principle", "file_type": "rationale", "source_file": "models/cortex.md", "source_location": null, "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "Central framing of the design: VRAM (storage) and compute (FLOPs/energy/speed) are independent axes \u2014 a lever that crushes one does not necessarily touch the other. Per cortex.md sec 1's table: ternary weights (BitNet b1.58) are the primary VRAM lever (mult->add) and also help compute; hybrid GDN+SWA attention bounds VRAM (no exploding KV-cache) and cuts compute (linear vs quadratic); ReLU^2 activation sparsity only helps compute; MoR (weight-tying) helps both VRAM and compute; MoE only helps compute, not VRAM, and is reserved for scale. Winning duo for VRAM specifically: ternary + weight-tying via MoR."}, {"id": "benchmark_piqa", "label": "PiQA", "file_type": "concept", "source_file": "models/cortex.md", "source_location": null, "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null}, {"id": "benchmark_arc", "label": "ARC (ARC-easy / ARC-challenge)", "file_type": "concept", "source_file": "models/cortex.md", "source_location": null, "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null}, {"id": "benchmark_hellaswag", "label": "HellaSwag", "file_type": "concept", "source_file": "models/cortex.md", "source_location": null, "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null}, {"id": "benchmark_winogrande", "label": "Winogrande", "file_type": "concept", "source_file": "models/cortex.md", "source_location": null, "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null}, {"id": "paper_bitnet_b158", "label": "BitNet b1.58 \u2014 The Era of 1-bit LLMs (Ma et al., arXiv:2402.17764)", "file_type": "paper", "source_file": "models/cortex.md", "source_location": null, "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null}, {"id": "paper_bitnet_b158_2b4t", "label": "BitNet b1.58 2B4T technical report (arXiv:2504.12285)", "file_type": "paper", "source_file": "models/cortex.md", "source_location": null, "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null}, {"id": "paper_gated_delta_networks", "label": "Gated Delta Networks: Improving Mamba2 with Delta Rule (Yang et al., arXiv:2412.06464)", "file_type": "paper", "source_file": "models/cortex.md", "source_location": null, "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null}, {"id": "paper_mixture_of_depths", "label": "Mixture-of-Depths (Raposo et al., arXiv:2404.02258)", "file_type": "paper", "source_file": "models/cortex.md", "source_location": null, "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null}, {"id": "paper_mixture_of_recursions", "label": "Mixture-of-Recursions (arXiv:2507.10524)", "file_type": "paper", "source_file": "models/cortex.md", "source_location": null, "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null}, {"id": "paper_lazy_neuron_phenomenon", "label": "T